WEBVTT

00:18.066 --> 00:20.600
You're in Springwood now.

00:20.666 --> 00:22.533
And you're all mine!

01:30.866 --> 01:35.400
Oh great spirit
of William Murdoch..

01:35.466 --> 01:39.933
...first mate
of the great ship Titanic.

01:40.000 --> 01:41.933
Are you there?

01:44.500 --> 01:46.433
William Murdoch.

01:48.000 --> 01:51.100
If you are there, I invite you..

01:51.166 --> 01:54.133
...to use my earthly body..

01:54.200 --> 01:58.466
...my vocal chords,
my very soul as your channel

01:58.533 --> 02:01.533
to the world of the living.

02:01.600 --> 02:03.533
Speak to us.

02:04.733 --> 02:07.300
Speak to us.

02:08.300 --> 02:09.300
Spe-ak!

02:15.666 --> 02:17.600
I am here!

02:19.266 --> 02:23.433
William Murdoch, first mate
reporting for duty.

02:25.533 --> 02:26.866
Oh, my God!

02:26.933 --> 02:29.066
Look! Dead ahead!

02:29.133 --> 02:30.900
A huge iceberg!

02:30.966 --> 02:34.300
Oh! Engines full stop!

02:35.033 --> 02:36.166
My God!

02:36.233 --> 02:37.900
It's too late!

02:37.966 --> 02:39.700
Oh!

02:39.766 --> 02:42.000
All engines, full reverse!

02:42.066 --> 02:44.133
- Ah!
- 'Is she alright?'

02:45.966 --> 02:48.366
We're taking on water!

02:48.433 --> 02:50.900
We should have seen it coming!

02:50.966 --> 02:53.733
Wasn't anyone
watching the sonar?

02:53.800 --> 02:54.833
'Fraud!'

02:54.900 --> 02:58.066
Sonar wasn't invented
when the Titanic sailed!

02:58.133 --> 02:59.366
Ladies and gentlemen.

02:59.433 --> 03:02.200
I am Dr. Harry Lee,
professional skeptic.

03:02.266 --> 03:06.300
Ms. Mara Ruleen has just
proven herself a fraud!

03:06.366 --> 03:08.833
I feel myself drifting!

03:08.900 --> 03:11.366
Drifting..

03:12.600 --> 03:16.600
Sonar wasn't invented
when the Titanic sailed!

03:16.666 --> 03:20.200
- Fake! Fake!
- Refund!

03:20.266 --> 03:22.333
'Fake! Fake!'

03:48.933 --> 03:51.033
That chick
shouldn't mess with the dead.

03:51.100 --> 03:53.233
Take it from me. I'm dead.

03:54.833 --> 03:55.900
Hey.

03:55.966 --> 03:58.266
Maybe she could channel me.

04:09.066 --> 04:10.633
- You Mara Ruleen?
- Yes.

04:10.700 --> 04:12.366
- Who are you?
- Oliver Michaels.

04:12.433 --> 04:13.766
Hey, racky-rock!

04:13.833 --> 04:15.600
Uh, it's a touchstone.

04:15.666 --> 04:17.033
Listen, am I supposed
to know who you are?

04:17.100 --> 04:19.200
Uh-uh. Nope.

04:19.266 --> 04:21.700
Uh, then what do you want?

04:21.766 --> 04:23.966
Whoa. This sucker's heavy.

04:24.033 --> 04:25.833
What do you want?

04:25.900 --> 04:27.866
Well, I hear you're looking
for a new assistant.

04:27.933 --> 04:30.033
Look no further! I'm your man!

04:31.100 --> 04:32.533
You know..

04:32.600 --> 04:34.833
...your aura's real yellow.

04:35.933 --> 04:37.133
You read auras?

04:37.200 --> 04:38.166
That's my thing.

04:38.233 --> 04:40.866
That...and crystals.

04:40.933 --> 04:43.233
Wait. Did Harry Lee send you?

04:43.300 --> 04:45.466
- Harry who?
- Harry Lee!

04:45.533 --> 04:47.400
The slime ball
who spent the last year

04:47.466 --> 04:48.933
trying to ruin my career.

04:49.000 --> 04:50.433
Don't know him.

04:52.266 --> 04:54.000
Do you believe
a person can be a conduit

04:54.066 --> 04:57.366
through which the dead
can talk to the living?

04:57.433 --> 04:59.766
Listen, lady, I just need a job.

04:59.833 --> 05:01.600
I had this hot gig
with this lady photographer.

05:01.666 --> 05:05.133
It was great! Sexy babes
around all the time!

05:05.200 --> 05:07.166
Then she went blind
and my job went south.

05:07.233 --> 05:08.933
Just answer the question.

05:09.000 --> 05:10.700
Do you believe in channeling?

05:10.766 --> 05:12.700
I'll believe anything
if you pay me enough.

05:16.266 --> 05:18.200
I like your style.

05:20.066 --> 05:21.866
Ten dollars an hour enough?

05:21.933 --> 05:23.233
Racky! When do I start?

05:23.300 --> 05:24.733
Right now.

05:36.600 --> 05:38.333
Your job's very important, kid.

05:38.400 --> 05:40.666
You've got three
main responsibilities.

05:40.733 --> 05:42.933
Now, first and
most important, when I..

05:44.333 --> 05:45.833
'Watch this, man.'

05:48.033 --> 05:49.900
Ow!

05:49.966 --> 05:51.066
Hey. You listenin' to me?

05:51.133 --> 05:52.700
Yeah, yeah, I got
three responsibilities.

05:52.766 --> 05:55.200
Now, first and most important.

05:55.266 --> 05:58.700
When I'm on that stage,
although the channeling is fake

05:58.766 --> 06:01.333
the trance is real.
Helps me concentrate.

06:01.400 --> 06:04.866
Cool. What do you use, some kind
of transcendental trance?

06:04.933 --> 06:07.800
Well, something like that,
it's a very deep trance

06:07.866 --> 06:09.900
and it helps me
avoid stage fright.

06:09.966 --> 06:11.533
So where do I come in?

06:11.600 --> 06:12.566
You watch my back.

06:12.633 --> 06:13.633
Make sure none of those crazies

06:13.700 --> 06:14.800
jump on that stage with me

06:14.866 --> 06:16.166
Sort of a bouncer kind of thing.

06:16.233 --> 06:18.033
- Exactly.
- Ah.

06:18.100 --> 06:19.766
Hey, I recognize her.

06:19.833 --> 06:21.066
'Great set of pyramids.'

06:21.133 --> 06:22.333
Pay attention.

06:22.400 --> 06:24.900
Now your other two jobs
are taking the money at the door

06:24.966 --> 06:26.600
and watching the crowd.

06:26.666 --> 06:28.700
- What for?
- You look for suckers.

06:28.766 --> 06:31.166
You know, anybody who migh
be falling for my act

06:31.233 --> 06:32.700
hook, line, and sinker.

06:32.766 --> 06:33.900
You know, anybody
who might wanna pay

06:33.966 --> 06:35.900
big bucks
for a personal session.

06:35.966 --> 06:38.266
They usually look like this.

06:41.066 --> 06:42.633
Hey, you owe me
a hundred bucks, Ruleen!

06:42.700 --> 06:45.400
Oh, Barry Dean. How you doing?

06:45.466 --> 06:47.733
Oh, I'll be doing great as soon
as you pay that $100 you owe me.

06:47.800 --> 06:49.700
Oh, how do you know
I didn't win the bet?

06:49.766 --> 06:53.133
Well, can you top
$15,000 in three hours?

06:53.200 --> 06:55.433
Fifteen thousand in three hours?

06:55.500 --> 06:56.733
Yeah, you're gonna love this!

06:56.800 --> 06:58.133
Can I talk in front of, um..

06:58.200 --> 07:00.666
Oh, yeah, Barry Dean,
this is Oliver, he works for me.

07:00.733 --> 07:04.233
Oliver, meet one of my bes
friends and worst enemies.

07:04.300 --> 07:05.366
- How you doing?
- Barry Dean.

07:05.433 --> 07:07.066
Ha ha! Alright, now
you're gonna love this!

07:07.133 --> 07:09.433
So last week, this rich, old
Hollywood producer comes to me

07:09.500 --> 07:11.433
convinced that
his mansion is haunted

07:11.500 --> 07:12.533
by one of the Three Stooges.

07:12.600 --> 07:13.966
No!

07:14.033 --> 07:16.366
So I convinced him he had
the other two stooges, too.

07:16.433 --> 07:17.900
- You're kidding!
- 'Yeah!'

07:19.600 --> 07:21.733
At 5000 a spook..

07:21.800 --> 07:23.533
...I made 15 grand
in three hours.

07:23.600 --> 07:25.266
Read it and weep,

07:26.433 --> 07:28.266
Okay, you win.

07:28.333 --> 07:30.233
I'll pay you later.

07:30.300 --> 07:31.533
Oh, uh, listen.

07:31.600 --> 07:32.900
Has Harry Lee been around?

07:32.966 --> 07:34.266
I go on about an hour.

07:34.333 --> 07:36.833
No, but I'll keep
my eyes out for him.

07:36.900 --> 07:38.100
Oh, thanks.

07:38.166 --> 07:39.533
Come on, kid.

07:39.600 --> 07:41.066
What was that bet all about?

07:41.133 --> 07:43.333
Oh, we had a bet as to
who could make the most money

07:43.400 --> 07:46.033
from one sucker
at one time before the New Year.

07:46.100 --> 07:48.000
Really? What's the most
you ever made?

07:48.066 --> 07:49.300
Ten grand.

07:49.366 --> 07:52.166
Ah, but I've got a feeling
my luck's gonna change.

07:52.233 --> 07:54.233
Yeah, I think you've got
a good eye for suckers.

07:54.300 --> 07:55.700
Pick me out a juicy one.

07:55.766 --> 07:58.900
Oh, now, stay here. The crowd's
gonna be coming in any time.

08:08.266 --> 08:12.300
Oh, great spirit
of William Murdoch..

08:12.366 --> 08:15.966
...first mate
on the great ship Titanic.

08:16.033 --> 08:18.000
Are you there?

08:19.733 --> 08:21.633
William Murdoch..

08:21.700 --> 08:25.900
...if you are there I invite you
to use my earthly body.

08:25.966 --> 08:28.233
'My vocal chords.'

08:28.300 --> 08:30.666
'My soul!'

08:30.733 --> 08:33.433
'As your channel
to the world of the living..'

08:34.233 --> 08:36.600
...speak to us.

08:36.666 --> 08:38.433
Speak to...ugh!

08:43.800 --> 08:47.633
Don't mind if I do, ba-a-abe!

08:49.966 --> 08:52.600
Who's there?

08:52.666 --> 08:56.033
It ain't Mickey Mouse!

09:03.500 --> 09:06.133
Mara, snap out of it!
Mara, snap out of it!

09:08.600 --> 09:11.633
Don't get all red
in the face, boys!

09:15.266 --> 09:17.300
What's everyone staring at?

09:17.366 --> 09:19.333
Let's party!

09:23.933 --> 09:25.433
Are you sure you're okay?

09:25.500 --> 09:27.066
Yes. Now leave me alone.

09:27.133 --> 09:28.700
- Can we get you anything?
- No.

09:28.766 --> 09:30.466
Water?
Something to help you sleep?

09:30.533 --> 09:32.500
No! Just go away!

09:33.966 --> 09:36.200
Hey, I don't mind tellin' ya.

09:36.266 --> 09:39.733
That was the best performance
you've ever given.

09:39.800 --> 09:40.800
How'd you do
that thing to your voice

09:40.866 --> 09:42.933
to make it sound so ugly?

09:43.000 --> 09:44.233
Like this!

09:44.300 --> 09:46.533
Now, scat!

09:48.933 --> 09:50.900
I wonder what's gotten into her.

10:23.333 --> 10:24.633
Where am I?

10:24.700 --> 10:27.300
You're in a trance, doll face.

10:28.500 --> 10:31.466
Oh! What do you mean,
I'm in a trance?

10:31.533 --> 10:33.133
I'm wide awake!

10:33.200 --> 10:35.033
I'm right here in this, this..

10:35.100 --> 10:37.033
Trance.

10:38.100 --> 10:39.466
Who are you?

10:39.533 --> 10:41.233
Well, you said
you need a dead person

10:41.300 --> 10:43.133
that you could talk through.

10:43.200 --> 10:45.733
I'm your guy.

10:45.800 --> 10:47.733
I don't understand.

10:49.266 --> 10:50.900
Your body..

10:50.966 --> 10:53.266
...is my body, babe.

10:53.333 --> 10:56.933
And what a body it is!

11:06.600 --> 11:07.933
Red.

11:08.000 --> 11:09.933
Very...red.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.833
Uh, sorry.
I just didn't, you were..

11:11.900 --> 11:13.966
Uh, may I help you?

11:14.033 --> 11:15.266
Now, that's red.

11:15.333 --> 11:16.800
Definitely red.

11:16.866 --> 11:17.800
Excuse me?

11:17.866 --> 11:19.800
Your aura. Very red.

11:19.866 --> 11:22.166
- So is your face, pal.
- Thank you!

11:22.233 --> 11:24.366
Would you like to know
about my pyramids?

11:24.433 --> 11:25.833
Yes.

11:25.900 --> 11:28.266
- Very much.
- Okay.

11:28.333 --> 11:30.333
They're a natural source
of aura energy--

11:30.400 --> 11:32.100
Don't I know you from somewhere?

11:32.166 --> 11:33.800
I doubt it.

11:33.866 --> 11:36.366
Yeah, you posed
for Stony Adler once!

11:36.433 --> 11:38.366
- How did you know that?
- I was her assistant.

11:38.433 --> 11:39.666
Oh, yeah.

11:39.733 --> 11:41.733
You were that jerk
that kept hitting on me.

11:41.800 --> 11:42.933
That's me!

11:43.000 --> 11:44.600
So. You still modeling?

11:44.666 --> 11:46.666
No. After my, uh..

11:46.733 --> 11:48.700
...experience with
that weirdo photographer

11:48.766 --> 11:50.700
I swore it off.

11:50.766 --> 11:54.466
Uh, would you like to
know about my pyramids, sir?

11:54.533 --> 11:56.066
Actually, I was wondering

11:56.133 --> 11:59.033
if you could direct me
to a good trans-channeler.

11:59.100 --> 12:02.300
I need to contact my dead father
as soon as possible.

12:02.366 --> 12:03.700
I know a good channeler.

12:03.766 --> 12:06.133
- Who is it?
- It's Mara Ruleen.

12:06.200 --> 12:08.233
But I don't know if she wants
to be bothered right now.

12:08.300 --> 12:09.966
Uh, who are you?

12:10.033 --> 12:12.100
I'm her assistant.

12:12.166 --> 12:14.566
You're Mara Ruleen's assistant?

12:14.633 --> 12:16.100
Where can I find her?

12:16.166 --> 12:17.733
I'll pay anything!

12:17.800 --> 12:19.400
- Anything?
- Hmm.

12:20.700 --> 12:22.966
She's in room 243. Go on up.

12:23.033 --> 12:24.566
And be sure to tell her
what you just told me.

12:24.633 --> 12:27.400
Especially the part
about paying her anything.

12:27.466 --> 12:28.733
Thank you!

12:29.900 --> 12:31.033
Uh!

12:31.100 --> 12:32.600
Be sure you tell her
Oliver sent you.

12:32.666 --> 12:34.400
Mm.

12:34.466 --> 12:36.400
Oliver? Uh, sweetheart.

12:36.466 --> 12:39.000
Would you watch
my booth till I get back?

12:39.066 --> 12:40.633
- Sure.
- Thanks.

12:47.066 --> 12:48.466
What did you tell
that guy just now?

12:48.533 --> 12:50.233
I just told him
where he could find Mara.

12:50.300 --> 12:51.900
He's got big bucks,
I could smell it.

12:51.966 --> 12:55.400
You idiot!
That is Harry Lee! Come on

12:57.066 --> 13:00.266
Couldn't have picked
a better body to live in.

13:00.333 --> 13:03.833
Bet you're
a real man-killer, huh.

13:03.900 --> 13:05.800
Hey!

13:05.866 --> 13:08.733
Put my clothes back on!

13:08.800 --> 13:12.400
You perverted, ugly, mean..
Hey!

13:12.466 --> 13:14.066
'Ms. Ruleen?'

13:14.133 --> 13:16.200
'It's Harry Lee.'

13:16.266 --> 13:18.966
What do you say
we kill us a man?

13:26.100 --> 13:28.066
Say something!

13:28.133 --> 13:31.066
When are you gonna
let me go, you bastard?

13:31.133 --> 13:33.966
When are you gonna
let me go, you bastard?

13:34.033 --> 13:35.766
Put my clothes back on!

13:35.833 --> 13:38.266
Put my clothes back on!

13:38.333 --> 13:40.500
Rich Little, eat your heart out.

13:55.266 --> 13:56.866
Ms. Ruleen! I, uh..

13:56.933 --> 13:58.466
...oh, I-I didn't mean to, uh--

13:58.533 --> 14:01.400
Hello, uh, uh, old friend.

14:01.466 --> 14:04.100
How are you? Come in.

14:04.200 --> 14:05.433
Sit.

14:05.500 --> 14:07.266
Help, Harry!

14:07.333 --> 14:10.266
Harry! Harry!

14:10.333 --> 14:12.333
Shut up, bitch!

14:12.400 --> 14:14.366
He can't hear you.

14:14.433 --> 14:16.166
I beg your pardon.

14:16.233 --> 14:19.266
Uh, nothing,
just talking to myself.

14:19.333 --> 14:21.800
Sit.

14:21.866 --> 14:23.433
Si-i-t.

14:30.200 --> 14:33.300
Ms. Ruleen, I hope
you don't mind my interrupting.

14:33.366 --> 14:34.900
Uh, my name's Jodi.

14:34.966 --> 14:36.366
I've wanted to meet you
ever since--

14:36.433 --> 14:38.833
We have met, bimbo.

14:38.900 --> 14:40.033
I beg your pardon?

14:41.266 --> 14:42.600
'We could've danced all night.'

14:42.666 --> 14:44.500
Where do I know
that voice from?

14:44.566 --> 14:46.866
That weirdo
at the photography shoot.

14:46.933 --> 14:48.666
Uh, I-I'm sorry I interrupted.

14:48.733 --> 14:51.733
- I--
- Don't be silly, come on in.

14:51.800 --> 14:54.933
Excuse us, we women
have to powder our noses.

14:58.366 --> 15:00.266
What happened to your voice?

15:00.333 --> 15:02.333
Nothing. Why?

15:02.400 --> 15:05.466
Uh, wh-what do you want from me?

15:05.533 --> 15:07.366
Just to look at you.

15:07.433 --> 15:10.166
Such a pretty face.

15:10.233 --> 15:13.766
Now, listen, I don't go
for that kind of stuff.

15:13.833 --> 15:15.700
What kind of stuff?

15:15.766 --> 15:17.366
I-I mean, I think
you're pretty and all

15:17.433 --> 15:20.366
but I like men, not women.

15:20.433 --> 15:22.833
You're a real head-turner, babe.

15:24.366 --> 15:25.433
No!

15:25.500 --> 15:27.233
'Yeah!'

15:27.300 --> 15:28.800
You killed her.

15:30.566 --> 15:32.200
'Wasn't that fun?'

15:32.266 --> 15:35.566
'What do you say
we do it again?'

15:35.633 --> 15:38.100
No! Please, no!

15:40.800 --> 15:43.766
Now, how 'bout a drink?

15:43.833 --> 15:46.900
Oh-h. Now that would be nice.

15:46.966 --> 15:50.033
- Name your poison.
- How about a bloody Mary?

15:50.100 --> 15:52.300
Hmm, I'll see
if I've got that.

15:54.300 --> 15:55.533
Oh, sorry.

15:56.600 --> 15:59.966
I can't make you a bloody Mary.

16:00.033 --> 16:03.566
How about I make you
a bloody Harry?

16:13.866 --> 16:15.333
No!

16:15.400 --> 16:17.400
'Yes!'

16:26.766 --> 16:28.300
Huh?

16:33.000 --> 16:35.200
Come on in, boys.

16:35.266 --> 16:37.233
The more the merrier.

16:42.166 --> 16:43.933
Let me go!

16:44.000 --> 16:46.233
You murderer!

16:46.300 --> 16:48.233
Call me crazy
but it looks to me

16:48.300 --> 16:50.233
like you're
the murderer, babe.

16:51.266 --> 16:54.433
You're right.
They'll think I did it.

16:54.500 --> 16:56.366
I'll get the death sentence
for this.

16:56.433 --> 16:59.533
Ah, don't worry. Maybe
some weirdo can channel you.

17:00.600 --> 17:02.366
Uh, let me go!

17:02.433 --> 17:05.200
Not a chance,
I'm having too much fun.

17:05.266 --> 17:07.833
Fun? You call killing fun?

17:07.900 --> 17:10.133
Who were you
when you were alive?

17:10.200 --> 17:11.966
An axe murderer?

17:12.033 --> 17:13.433
You're gettin' warm.

17:13.500 --> 17:15.400
Uh, you're insane.

17:15.466 --> 17:18.566
I know, isn't it great?

17:18.633 --> 17:20.600
This is all an act, right?

17:20.666 --> 17:23.400
Hello, Barry.

17:23.466 --> 17:25.633
I mean, uh, hello, Barry.

17:25.700 --> 17:28.666
Oliver.
Oh, well, come on in.

17:28.733 --> 17:31.800
Oh, close the door!

17:35.133 --> 17:37.800
Oh, uh, don't mind him.
He's dead.

17:37.866 --> 17:41.700
Uh, I mean, uh,
he-he killed himself.

17:41.766 --> 17:43.200
Yeah-yeah that's right.

17:43.266 --> 17:44.533
Oh, yeah, the-the poor man

17:44.600 --> 17:47.166
he-he just killed himself!

17:47.233 --> 17:50.700
- I see.
- You don't believe me.

17:50.766 --> 17:52.800
Oh, no, of course I believe you.

17:52.866 --> 17:54.566
This is an act, right?
That's fake blood?

17:54.633 --> 17:56.100
I don't think so.
I've seen this once before.

17:56.166 --> 17:57.366
She's stuck
in some kind of trance.

17:57.433 --> 17:58.500
What does that mean?

17:58.566 --> 17:59.566
It means she might
really have some kind of

17:59.633 --> 18:01.100
weird spirit using her body.

18:01.166 --> 18:02.366
We have to get her
out of this trance.

18:02.433 --> 18:03.666
So how do we do that?

18:03.733 --> 18:04.900
You ever see "The Exorcist?"

18:04.966 --> 18:06.966
- Yeah, ten times.
- Good.

18:07.033 --> 18:09.700
Good. We're about to perform
an exorcism.

18:09.766 --> 18:10.900
- We're not priests.
- We don't have to be.

18:10.966 --> 18:12.166
There's only one thing
that can motivate her

18:12.233 --> 18:14.866
out of this trance
and it sure ain't religion

18:14.933 --> 18:16.533
Then what is it?

18:18.166 --> 18:20.033
- Power of money compels you.
- Power of money compels you.

18:20.100 --> 18:22.666
The power of money compels you.

18:22.733 --> 18:24.833
'The power of money
compels you.'

18:24.900 --> 18:27.100
'The power of money
